# DineFlow Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Overview
- **Name:** DineFlow v2.1
- **Stack:** Turborepo + Next.js 15 (App Router) + NestJS 10 + GraphQL + PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM + Redis + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- **Package Manager:** pnpm

## Folder Structure
- Frontend: `apps/web/` (no `src/` folder—files directly under `app/`, `components/`, `lib/`, `store/`, `hooks/`)
- Backend: `apps/api/`
- Documentation: `docs/`

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict mode—NO `any` without comment justification
- File naming: kebab-case (`user-profile.tsx`)
- Components: PascalCase (`MenuItemCard`)
- Functions: camelCase (`calculateTotalPrice`)
- Database tables/columns: snake_case

## Design System (Mobile-First)
- Primary color: `#F59E0B` (orange)
- Dark background: `#0F172A`
- Touch targets: ≥44px
- Modals: bottom sheets on mobile
- Toasts: `sonner`, positioned bottom-center

## Important Constraints
- NEVER create a `src/` folder—all frontend code goes directly under `apps/web/`
- Use absolute paths in file operations: `/home/dhz/PROJECTS/our/dineflow/apps/web/...`
- Preserve existing working code; only fix what's broken
- Read documentation in `docs/` before making major changes

## Current State (As of Migration from TRAE)
- Backend: Fully complete (Auth, Menu, Order, WebSocket modules) running on port 3001
- Frontend: 95% complete—missing homepage menu backend connection, some testing
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` starts both web (3000) and api (3001)

## When Generating Code
- Follow the patterns in existing files
- Use shadcn/ui components from `apps/web/components/ui/`
- Use Zustand stores from `apps/web/store/`
- Use Apollo Client configured in `apps/web/lib/apollo-client.ts`